name: Proto Seascape ***Genesis Drop***
description: This was the prototype/first brush painting I did for a series of larger seascapes that I subsequently painted and sold. The sketch turned out to be my favorite and is fitting that it is my genesis drop on hic et nunc. The sea os a rocky cliff on the Pacific coast and the seals read my Chinese painting name, given to me by my painting master, Ning Yeh, and my seal which reads "always experimenting."
